The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Computer sales fall 7%
                                                                                                               Computer sales fall 7%
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                              
	New Delhi, July 14: Sales of personal computers in the last fiscal have declined 7 per cent to 67.9 lakh. During this period, Internet users grew 19 per cent to 600 lakh.        
	According to data released by the Manufacturers Association of Information Technology (MAIT), sales of desktops dipped 4 per cent to 52.7 lakh, while notebook sales fell 17 per cent to 15.1 lakh.        
	Internet entities  companies and households with connections  increased to 86 lakh in 2008-09 compared with 72 lakh in the previous year.         
	According to Vinnie Mehta, executive director of the MAIT, Sales have been impacted by restrained demand from the BPO, retail, IT and SME segments due to liquidity concerns and general economic performance. Household consumption was also muted due to concerns of job security.         
	The MAIT expects positive growth for PCs and other IT products in 2009-10.         
	Among enterprises, the major buyers were telecom, banking and educational institutions.                                                                                                                                        
